Chocolates Exploration by Dlaivison R. Silva

The Objective of this exploration is to identify the cocoa market and its variances. The consumption of chocolate in the world is increasing every year. Several people prefers also best quality chocolates instead of popular brands. Similar to wine and cofee the cocoa also has different types of beans and flavors. The current dataset shows ratings of the cocoa quality and its origin.

To understand and classify the best chocolate beans and relate them to the main manufacturers. The main question to answer here is Does the best bean means the best chocolate ?

Reflection

During my research several types of analysis have been performed. From univariate analysis the focus was to see the distribution of the main variables (rating, percent of cocoa, number of samples) per manufacturing company, country and Bean exporter. At this level some important points were take in consideration for the second level of analysis at Bivariate section. For Bivariate analysis, the main focus was to find a correlation between certain values. The variables Cocoa Percent and Rating has shown some linearity between the interval of 65-75 % (cocoa percent). The bean types Amazon and Blend Forastero were the best types found on this research At Multivariate analysis the main target was to determine the correlation factor between the cocoa percent and rating and have the linear function to interpret the values. No model has been built due the limitation of variables and data. There were several challenges on this project. As the data set has no numerical variables I needed to built some intermediate variables to have a better interpretation of the data. These intermediate variables were used to evaluate and better determine the correlation and judge the best companies, countries and bean types. I learned also how to manipulate the geographic maps in my research. Because plotting only the countriess names was not enough than plotting the regions. In terms of data analysis the data interpretation is a key. I believe this dataset must be improved and should contains new variables, such as bean granularity, type_of_use (for which use the chocolate is designated), acid levels , etc. In my research I have noticed the companies focus more in percentage level of 70% than other levels, so therefore this percentage should be considered the main in terms of research.
